  "prompt": "Who is Bruce Wayne?",
  "response": "Bruce Wayne is a fictional character and the alter ego of Batman, a superhero featured in DC Comics. Created by artist Bob Kane and writer Bill Finger, Bruce Wayne first appeared in \"Detective Comics\" #27 in 1939. \n\nBruce Wayne is a billionaire industrialist, philanthropist, and owner of Wayne Enterprises. As a child, he witnessed the murder of his parents, Thomas and Martha Wayne, which profoundly impacted him and led him to dedicate his life to fighting crime. After years of rigorous physical and intellectual training, Bruce adopted the persona of Batman to strike fear into the hearts of criminals and protect the citizens of Gotham City.\n\nBatman is known for his lack of superpowers, relying instead on his detective skills, physical prowess, advanced technology, and strategic mind to combat crime. Bruce Wayne's dual identity allows him to operate in both the corporate world and the shadowy streets of Gotham, often balancing his role as a businessman with his nightly crusades as the Caped Crusader.",
